
# ── INTERNAL API TOKEN (Edge SSR auth header) ────────────────────────
# Shared secret between SSR egress and the CDN's WAF rule. Lets SSR
# fetches skip the CDN's bot mitigation so SSR-rendered pages don't
# 404/degrade intermittently when the CDN flags Vercel/Netlify
# serverless egress as bot traffic.
#
# This MUST be a server-side env var. Do NOT prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_
# (the value must not be exposed to the browser).
#
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# Set in your hosting platform's env settings (Production + Preview).
# Configure the matching CDN WAF rule (see docs/edge-ssr-auth-header.md).
INTERNAL_API_TOKEN=
